    <item>
      <title>4C FCPdf External Library - Examples</title>
      <link>https://github.com/ashish-kus/4C_docs/docs/features/extlibs/fcpdf/examples/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://github.com/ashish-kus/4C_docs/docs/features/extlibs/fcpdf/examples/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/ashish-kus/4C_docs/docs/features/extlibs/&#34;&gt;4C External Libraries Home&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/ashish-kus/4C_docs/docs/features/extlibs/fcpdf/&#34;&gt;FCPdf Home&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Example 1 - fcpdf.demo.1 This should be a simple program to follow. It allows you to select a font, a fontsize, x and y positions in points and some text to write. Clicking a button then will create one pdf file with one page and one line of text. Clicking another button will show the newly created PDF file in a client pdf viewer program.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Example 2 - fcpdf.demo.2 This program shows a few more things that you can do, including setting stroke colors, drawing lines, and measuring text width. The program creates a pdf file of a red grid of a user chosen size. Row and column numbers or markers are printed in the outside grid boxes. You can actually create a form that works for measuring positions on another pre printed form.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All of the above examples are in the 4c demo application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you need to download the most recent 4c demo programs here&amp;rsquo;s the link:
&lt;a href=&#34;https://4csoftware.com/downloads/misc/demo.tar.gz&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;4C Demo Application Back to Top&lt;svg class=&#34;hx:inline hx:rtl:rotate-270 hx:align-baseline&#34; height=&#34;1em&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;
 &lt;path d=&#34;m9.1716 7.7574h7.0711m0 0v7.0711m0-7.0711-8.4853 8.4853&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;/&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

      </description>
    </item>
    
